Falcon 9â€™s first stage booster previously supported SpaceXâ€™s Crew-1 and Crew-2 missions, which launched astronauts to the International Space Station, and launch of SXM-8. The Dragon spacecraft supporting this mission previously supported SpaceXâ€™s 21st Commercial Resupply Services (CRS-21) mission. Dragon will separate from Falcon 9â€™s second stage about twelve minutes after liftoff and autonomously dock to the space station on Monday, August 30 at approximately 11:00 a.m. EDT, 15:00 UTC.
